00:22:38,774 --> 00:22:41,359
- Not like last time.
- [PEÑA] Last time?

311
00:22:42,152 --> 00:22:43,195
The CIA.

312
00:22:43,695 --> 00:22:46,573
They had us out here hunting
commies on Christmas day.

313
00:22:46,656 --> 00:22:49,409
- That's real dedication.
- It is God's work.

314
00:22:50,494 --> 00:22:52,037
Merry Christmas.

315
00:23:09,763 --> 00:23:12,641
[DAVID] My dad trusts him,
but... did you see him?

316
00:23:12,724 --> 00:23:15,018
[DARÍO] That son of a bitch
looks nervous, right?

317
00:23:15,102 --> 00:23:19,481
[DAVID] Never stopped
adjusting the mirror, staring.

318
00:23:19,564 --> 00:23:22,234
I kind of love how much
this motherfucker hates me.

319
00:23:22,317 --> 00:23:24,027
[DAVID AND DARÍO CHUCKLE]

320
00:23:24,653 --> 00:23:27,155
[DAVID] Our man in Bogotá confirmed
there must be an informant.

321
00:23:27,239 --> 00:23:28,365
[DARÍO] Huh?

322
00:23:28,448 --> 00:23:31,576
[DAVID] Salcedo has to be the one
the gringos are calling "Natalia."

323
00:23:31,660 --> 00:23:34,412
I'm going to love killing
that motherfucker.

324
00:23:34,496 --> 00:23:38,041
You know who else I am going
to kill? His arrogant wife.

325
00:23:38,625 --> 00:23:40,877
I'm going to leave those
poor girls orphans.

326
00:23:40,961 --> 00:23:42,420
[DARÍO] Poor things.

327
00:23:42,504 --> 00:23:43,713
[DAVID] You can adopt them.

328
00:23:43,797 --> 00:23:46,299
[LAUGHS] You son of a bitch...

329
00:23:49,594 --> 00:23:51,429
[SHUDDERS]

330
00:23:53,807 --> 00:23:55,976
[BEEPING]

331
00:23:57,853 --> 00:23:59,729
[PHONE RINGING]

332
00:24:00,313 --> 00:24:01,398
Answer.

333
00:24:05,235 --> 00:24:07,737
[PAOLA ON VOICE MAIL] This
is Paola, leave a message.

334
00:24:07,821 --> 00:24:09,072
Hello, love, it's me.

335
00:24:09,156 --> 00:24:12,409
Paola, listen,
I need you to call me back.

336
00:24:12,492 --> 00:24:14,077
It's very important.

337
00:24:37,976 --> 00:24:39,060
3 NEW MESSAGES

338
00:24:39,144 --> 00:24:41,062
DELETE?

339
00:24:41,146 --> 00:24:42,939
CONFIRM

340
00:24:43,023 --> 00:24:44,399
0 NEW MESSAGES

341
00:25:13,803 --> 00:25:15,513
[CAR APPROACHING]

342
00:25:23,146 --> 00:25:24,356
[KNOCKING]

343
00:25:35,617 --> 00:25:38,161
Take me to where you
stashed him, Jorge Salcedo.

344
00:25:41,248 --> 00:25:42,582
Stashed who?

345
00:25:45,423 --> 00:25:46,583
Pallomari.

346
00:25:49,256 --> 00:25:51,007
Are we taking him someplace?

347
00:25:51,967 --> 00:25:53,009
Uh-uh.

348
00:25:55,428 --> 00:25:56,594
I see.

349
00:26:07,232 --> 00:26:09,109
What do you mean,
you're going to a meeting?

350
00:26:10,318 --> 00:26:12,654
I have a business to run, Guillermo.

351
00:26:12,737 --> 00:26:13,863
A meeting with who?

352
00:26:14,656 --> 00:26:17,701
With Fredy. We're meeting a new client.

353
00:26:17,784 --> 00:26:22,122
Fredy? Patricia, the police
almost caught Miguel yesterday.

354
00:26:23,206 --> 00:26:24,207
For fuck's sake.

355
00:26:24,874 --> 00:26:26,501
What's the problem?

356
00:26:26,876 --> 00:26:29,004
You didn't tell them
where he was, did you?

357
00:26:29,087 --> 00:26:31,423
- No.
- No. What are you worried about?

358
00:26:31,506 --> 00:26:34,509
Miguel likes you.
That's what you always tell me.

359
00:26:34,592 --> 00:26:36,553
Yes, but always within limits.

360
00:26:37,137 --> 00:26:39,222
You're worrying too much, Guillermo.

361
00:26:39,306 --> 00:26:42,934
They need you. You're the brains
behind the organization...

362
00:26:42,941 --> 00:26:44,723
None of that matters, Patricia,

363
00:26:44,730 --> 00:26:48,732
none, if they decide not
to leave loose ends.

364
00:26:49,357 --> 00:26:51,568
You're giving me a headache.

365
00:26:54,195 --> 00:26:55,196
Listen to me.

366
00:26:56,239 --> 00:26:59,826
My love, we have to get out
of here before it's too late.

367
00:27:12,672 --> 00:27:14,215
It's just a couple hours.

368
00:27:17,719 --> 00:27:19,679
Call me if there's a problem.

369
00:27:25,435 --> 00:27:26,686
[DOOR OPENS]

370
00:27:30,899 --> 00:27:35,153
["ESPÉRAME EN EL CIELO"
PLAYING ON RADIO]

371
00:27:40,158 --> 00:27:41,993
What is it, Jorge Salcedo?

372
00:27:44,662 --> 00:27:48,249
What do we do if we find Pallomari's
family in the apartment?

373
00:27:50,335 --> 00:27:51,836
Hope that we don't.

374
00:27:55,340 --> 00:27:59,344
We'll need to be quick.
I have someplace to be.

375
00:28:01,888 --> 00:28:07,560
The love of my life is in
town and we have a date.

376
00:28:10,647 --> 00:28:11,731
That's great.

377
00:28:12,440 --> 00:28:14,359
When was the last time you saw her?

378
00:28:15,026 --> 00:28:16,277
Eight years.

379
00:28:17,987 --> 00:28:19,823
Eight long years.

380
00:28:20,782 --> 00:28:23,701
Why so long since last time you saw her?

381
00:28:23,785 --> 00:28:27,580
You know, she was abroad.

382
00:28:28,289 --> 00:28:30,750
- In Japan.
- Japan?

383
00:28:32,168 --> 00:28:33,169
Working?

384
00:28:35,171 --> 00:28:37,882
She fucked a police captain.

385
00:28:39,259 --> 00:28:40,510
Then tried to turn me in.

386
00:28:41,177 --> 00:28:44,639
All these years, I've been
hanging around her parents' house

387
00:28:44,723 --> 00:28:46,474
waiting for her to come back.

388
00:28:47,142 --> 00:28:52,522
People say things happen for a reason.
All I know is... she came back.

389
00:28:53,189 --> 00:28:54,274
She came back.

390
00:28:59,738 --> 00:29:01,948
Beautiful day. Right?

391
00:29:05,201 --> 00:29:06,953
How many tents, give or take?

392
00:29:08,204 --> 00:29:09,706
I think around 20.

393
00:29:10,165 --> 00:29:14,169
The FARC arrange themselves in
staggered positions, two circles.

394
00:29:14,669 --> 00:29:19,215
Then they always go for lookouts
in high places along the trails.

395
00:29:19,299 --> 00:29:20,759
Sun sets in three hours.

396
00:29:21,468 --> 00:29:24,429
As soon as they hear the chopper,
they're going to hide.

397
00:29:24,512 --> 00:29:28,266
Generators, flashlights,
fires... everything.

398
00:29:28,349 --> 00:29:30,769
Those rats have a lot
of practice hiding.

399
00:29:31,060 --> 00:29:35,356
Once the lights go, they'll use
guidelines strung into the jungle.

400
00:29:36,065 --> 00:29:38,985
They grab hold, follow ropes to safety.

401
00:29:39,068 --> 00:29:44,324
Once we find one of those ropes...

402
00:29:44,407 --> 00:29:47,118
[IMITATES GUNFIRE]

403
00:29:47,827 --> 00:29:49,871
It's a fucking slaughter.

404
00:29:49,954 --> 00:29:50,955
Berna.

405
00:30:00,590 --> 00:30:02,634
[SOLDIERS COUNTING DOWN IN UNISON]

406
00:30:09,349 --> 00:30:12,352
Look, I don't want a bloodbath.

407
00:30:13,561 --> 00:30:14,854
Listen to me, Peña.

408
00:30:15,814 --> 00:30:17,232
You want the girl...

409
00:30:18,191 --> 00:30:19,984
there will be a body count.

410
00:30:20,068 --> 00:30:21,903
This is a war zone.

411
00:30:22,987 --> 00:30:26,825
But if you want, we can
still call this thing off.

412
00:30:30,703 --> 00:30:31,955
I need to get her back.

413
00:30:32,580 --> 00:30:33,748
[CHUCKLES]

414
00:30:35,041 --> 00:30:36,835
Just to be clear...

415
00:30:38,419 --> 00:30:40,713
something goes wrong...

416
00:30:41,339 --> 00:30:44,843
you still keep your promise.

417
00:31:06,948 --> 00:31:12,203
Hey, you talk to Pallomari,
try to keep him calm.

418
00:31:12,579 --> 00:31:14,998
- Then I come in.
- Okay.

419
00:31:17,292 --> 00:31:18,376
[EXHALES]

420
00:31:18,459 --> 00:31:20,565
[TELEVISION PLAYING IN DISTANCE]

421
00:31:20,572 --> 00:31:21,664
[KNOCKING]

422
00:31:21,671 --> 00:31:22,741
Pallomari.

423
00:31:24,716 --> 00:31:25,717
Pallomari!

424
00:31:50,950 --> 00:31:51,993
[EXHALES]

425
00:31:53,661 --> 00:31:54,746
[CHUCKLES]

426
00:31:57,332 --> 00:31:59,500
He's not here, of course.

427
00:32:00,877 --> 00:32:03,504
[SIGHING]

428
00:32:03,588 --> 00:32:04,881
No luggage.

429
00:32:06,925 --> 00:32:10,511
Must've freaked out when
Miguel almost got caught.

430
00:32:11,596 --> 00:32:15,433
You know, Pallomari, he's the smart one.

431
00:32:15,516 --> 00:32:16,726
[CHUCKLES]

432
00:32:16,809 --> 00:32:19,437
Guess that's why he's the accountant.

433
00:32:19,520 --> 00:32:20,939
And not a thug.

434
00:32:24,901 --> 00:32:26,110
Hey, Salcedo.

435
00:32:27,737 --> 00:32:29,322
You'll need to find him.

436
00:32:29,405 --> 00:32:31,991
Miguel gave this priority.
Do you understand?

437
00:32:32,075 --> 00:32:33,169
I'll take care of it.

438
00:32:34,202 --> 00:32:35,995
Let me know when you have him.

439
00:32:38,915 --> 00:32:41,834
I need tonight for the
business I told you about.

440
00:32:42,627 --> 00:32:43,795
Oh.

441
00:32:43,878 --> 00:32:44,879
Sure.

442
00:32:44,963 --> 00:32:46,381
[SIGHS]

443
00:32:48,466 --> 00:32:49,550
Good luck then.

444
00:32:59,394 --> 00:33:00,603
[BEEPING]

445
00:33:04,983 --> 00:33:07,026
[PHONE RINGING]

446
00:33:12,156 --> 00:33:15,618
- [JORGE] Hey, it's me.
- Salcedo! Busy today.

447
00:33:15,702 --> 00:33:16,736
Listen...

448
00:33:17,245 --> 00:33:19,080
any chatter from Pallomari?

449
00:33:19,163 --> 00:33:22,208
None I've heard. But we got him.

450
00:33:24,460 --> 00:33:26,337
- Who?
- Enrique.

451
00:33:27,296 --> 00:33:30,216
He called his brother, the idiot.

452
00:33:30,299 --> 00:33:32,176
David's on his way to get him.

453
00:33:33,845 --> 00:33:34,929
That's great news.

454
00:33:35,638 --> 00:33:37,598
Miguel must be pleased.

455
00:33:38,599 --> 00:33:39,636
[PHONE CLICKS]

456
00:33:52,196 --> 00:33:55,867
[PHONE RINGING]

457
00:34:03,583 --> 00:34:04,584
[BEEPS]

458
00:34:06,711 --> 00:34:08,588
- David?
- We have him.

459
00:34:10,214 --> 00:34:11,382
Yes?

460
00:34:12,508 --> 00:34:13,885
He showed up at the house?

461
00:34:14,343 --> 00:34:17,555
Meet us at 11th & 614th.

462
00:34:18,347 --> 00:34:19,682
[PHONE LINE CUTS]

463
00:34:29,567 --> 00:34:31,694
[BERNA] You ever hear
anything from Judy?

464
00:34:31,778 --> 00:34:33,571
[PEÑA] Not since you sold her out.

465
00:34:34,405 --> 00:34:37,325
Who would've thought it, Javier?
Both of us, bosses.

466
00:34:37,408 --> 00:34:39,952
They give you a nice place in Bogotá?

467
00:34:41,544 --> 00:34:42,573
It's good.

468
00:34:42,580 --> 00:34:44,082
You should see my house.

469
00:34:44,165 --> 00:34:47,659
I can take a shit in a different
bathroom every day of the week.

470
00:34:47,666 --> 00:34:48,722
My wife loves it.

471
00:34:50,046 --> 00:34:51,130
Your wife?

472
00:34:53,132 --> 00:34:54,967
I'm a family man.

473
00:34:56,177 --> 00:34:59,347
Bet you still live out of a suitcase.

474
00:34:59,430 --> 00:35:00,973
[BERNA CHUCKLES]

475
00:35:01,057 --> 00:35:02,934
Guess catching guys like me...

476
00:35:03,935 --> 00:35:06,938
